documentation.text:
@dev
 | The Trust Anchor Extra Data [Generic] reference contract
 | This contract is an example of the type of parameters most useful in a Data Retrieval context. Primarily, it is the ip addresses that are associated to a variable number of endpoints.
 | Endpoint names are also part of the context to have a human-readable structure, and this name is keccak hashed for future quick lookups internally.
@dev Event for Data Retrieval Endpoint is Enabled for a specific Endpoint name.
@dev Event for Data Retrieval Parameters being created by a Trust Anchor.
@dev Event for Data Retrieval Parameters being updated by a Trust Anchor.
@dev Mapping for a Trust Anchor to its generic extraData parameters.
@dev The Trust Anchor Manager address that this contract is bound to.
@dev Initializes this contract with the owner set to the calling public address.

@dev Gets the Trust Anchor Manager associated to this contract.
 @return result trust anchor manager address

devdoc.details: | The Trust Anchor Extra Data [Generic] reference contract | This contract is an example of the type of parameters most useful in a Data Retrieval context. Primarily, it is the ip addresses that are associated to a variable number of endpoints. | Endpoint names are also part of the context to have a human-readable structure, and this name is keccak hashed for future quick lookups internally.

EVT_setDataRetrievalParametersCreated(ad.details: Event for Data Retrieval Parameters being created by a Trust Anchor.

EVT_setDataRetrievalParametersUpdated(ad.details: Event for Data Retrieval Parameters being updated by a Trust Anchor.

EVT_setTrustAnchorDataRetrievalEndpointI.details: Event for Data Retrieval Endpoint is Enabled for a specific Endpoint name.

constructor.details: Initializes this contract with the owner set to the calling public address.

doesTrustAnchorHaveExtraData(address).details: Checks whether a specific Trust Anchor has extraData associated to it.

params._trustAnchorAddress: The smart contract address that is checked for extraData availability.

returns.result: | false: trust anchor has no extraData parameters allocated    | true: trust anchor does has extraData parameters allocated

getTrustAnchorDataRetrievalParameters(ad.details: Gets the data retrieval parameters (whether it exists, the actual endpoint data, and whether it's enabled) for this particular _endpointName.

params._trustAnchorAddress: The trust anchor address related to this extraData.

returns.doesExist: whether the endpoint data exists, ( false, [0, 0, 0, 0], false ): endpoint data does not exist

getTrustAnchorEndpointNameByEndpointKecc.details: Gets the endpoint name for a specific endpoint keccak for a Trust Anchor.

params._trustAnchorAddress: The trust anchor address related to this extraData.

returns.endpointName: endpoint data exists, returns the endpoint name

getTrustAnchorEndpointNameByIndex(addres.details: Gets the endpoint name for a specific index within the Trust Anchor's endpoint array.

params._index: The index within this Trust Anchor's endpoint array.
params._trustAnchorAddress: The trust anchor address related to this extraData.

returns.doesExist: whether the endpoint data exists, ( false, "" ): endpoint data does not exist

getTrustAnchorManagerAddress().details: Gets the Trust Anchor Manager associated to this contract.

getTrustAnchorNumberOfEndpoints(address).details: Gets the number of endpoints associated to this Trust Anchor.

params._trustAnchorAddress: The trust anchor address related to this extraData.

returns.result: the number of endpoints associated to this Trust Anchor.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setTrustAnchorDataRetrievalEndpointIsEna.details: Checks whether a specific Trust Anchor has "generic" extraData associated to it with a specific endpoint name, and updates the isEnabled if it already exists, and returns the status.

params._isEnabled: The boolean yes/no of whether this endpoint should be set to enabled or not.

returns.result: | 0: trust anchor is not verified    | 1: endpoint does not exist    | 2: endpoint's enabled status updated

setTrustAnchorDataRetrievalParameters(st.details: Checks whether a specific Trust Anchor has "generic" extraData associated to it with a specific endpoint name, updates if necessary, and returns the status. Sets the endpoint to "enabled" status if it's being set for the first time.

params._ipv4Address: The ipv4 address, an array of 4 uint8's (0-255) corresponding to w.x.y.z components of an ip address.

returns.result: | 0: trust anchor is not verified    | 1: endpoint set for the first time    | 2: endpoint updated

setTrustAnchorManagerAddress(address).details: Links Trust Anchor Manager to this contract's function flow.

params._trustAnchorManagerAddress: The smart contract address for the Trust Anchor Manager that should be linked.

returns.result: | false: [ will never return false due to require() ]    | true: trust anchor manager address set correctly

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

extraData_dataRetrievalParameters.details: Mapping for a Trust Anchor to its generic extraData parameters.

trustAnchorManagerAddress.details: The Trust Anchor Manager address that this contract is bound to.

getTrustAnchorEndpointNameByIndex(addres.notice: Checks to make sure that the _index parameter is not out of bounds.

setTrustAnchorDataRetrievalEndpointIsEna.notice: Must be called by the Trust Anchor that wants to set their associated generic data.

setTrustAnchorDataRetrievalParameters(st.notice: Must be called by the Trust Anchor that wants to set their associated generic data.
